In the program by the non-governmental organisation, whose mission is to professionalise sports in East Africa, the footballers will undergo trials under the watch of a Uefa licensed coachThe trials will be held in 11 Nairobi’s estates, namely; Mathare, Huruma, Kariobangi, Korogocho, Dandora, Kiambu, Kayole, Mukuru, Kibera, Kawangware and KangemiThe non-governmental organisation started the initiative with a men’s basketball trial between September and October last year, with more than 200 players between the age of 15 and 17 showing up, to try their luck Hundreds of budding male footballers in Nairobi, who are between the age of 17 and 19 years will from January 9 to February 5 battle it out for scholarship opportunities by Tusk Sports.
In the program by the non-governmental organisation, whose mission is to professionalise sports in East Africa, the footballers will undergo trials under the watch of a Uefa licensed coach.



