The best 22 players will be selected to benefit from the program.
The trials will be held in 11 Nairobi’s estates, namely; Mathare, Huruma, Kariobangi, Korogocho, Dandora, Kiambu, Kayole, Mukuru, Kibera, Kawangware and Kangemi.
According to Tusk Sports Camp Director Oluniyi Carew, the organisation will thereafter seek to secure academic and sporting opportunities through university scholarships in the United States of America, and trials with domestic and international professional football clubs.



