“We have had conversations with contacts in various teams and universities who are willing to consider the athletes we select. The agreement is that we have to provide them with top quality athletes,” said Carew, adding that they are in talks with a number of local football clubs, with a view to consider some of the players who will be selected.
The girls’ program will take place from February 13 to March 12.
Football is the second discipline, in which Tusk Sports is seeking to provide opportunities for athletes after basketball last year.
The non-governmental organisation started the initiative with a men’s basketball trial between September and October last year, with more than 200 players between the age of 15 and 17 showing up, to try their luck.



