According to Tusk Sports Coordinator Deng Garang, who was in charge of the basketball program, out of the 15 finalists (11 South Sudanese and 4 Kenyans), three have already landed scholarship opportunities at various universities in the United States of America.
They are 17-year-old Mathok Guot (Saint Louis University, Missouri), Xavier Yamo, 17, (Danville Christian Academy, Kentucky) and Ariik Kual, 16, (Capistrano Valley Christian School).
In the girl’s trial which took place between November and December, one girl out of the 15 finalists – Madina Okot has also landed a full scholarship opportunity at Saint Louis University in Missouri.
Garang expressed confidence that the organisation will find places for the remaining finalists since they are in talks with various institutions. Politicians led by Johnson Muthama, Susan Kihika and Kipchumba Murkomen say they have found peace and equality. The investigations have been narrowed down to close family members as well as the extended family. Employment Court quashed the appointment of Ms Wambui as the chairperson of the National Employment Authority.